CONCURRING, that we hereby acknowledge and commend the dedicated efforts of faith-based
recovery programs that have demonstrated a lasting commitment to helping individuals
overcome addiction and homelessness through faith-based principles and practices.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we encourage continued private and community
support for these organizations to empower their mission and work, recognizing that such
support is essential to sustaining their faith-based approach without dependence on public
funds.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we will advocate for partnerships and initiatives that
raise awareness about the positive impact of faith-based recovery programs on individuals,
families, and communities and explore avenues to celebrate and support their achievements
through public recognition, community events, and collaborative efforts with local service
providers.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we encourage organizations and stakeholders within
the State of Tennessee to learn from the example set by these faith-based recovery programs
and to collaborate in strengthening resources for individuals seeking recovery, renewal, and a
purposeful life grounded in faith.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
